      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Social Proof for Home Inspectors
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Buying a home is the biggest financial decision most people ever make. They need to trust their inspector completely — and that trust starts with other buyers saying "this inspector found what the other guy missed." SocialProof helps home inspectors capture and display those stories automatically.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Why buyers hire based on reputation</h2>
      <p>Most home inspectors get business through agent referrals — but that's changing. Buyers increasingly search for inspectors independently, read reviews, and choose based on credibility. If your website shows nothing but a phone number and a license number, you're invisible to the buyers who check online first.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;">A page of genuine testimonials from past clients — buyers who found issues, saved money, and felt protected — converts browsers into bookings.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">The testimonials that convert home inspection clients</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Thoroughness:</strong> "Found a roof issue, faulty wiring, and a cracked foundation wall that the seller's disclosure never mentioned. Worth every penny."</li>
        <li><strong>Report quality:</strong> "The report was detailed with photos, clearly written, and I could share it directly with my attorney."</li>
        <li><strong>Communication:</strong> "Walked through every finding with me and explained what was urgent vs. cosmetic. Never felt rushed."</li>
        <li><strong>Availability:</strong> "Booked same-week even in a competitive market. Flexible scheduling made a stressful process a little easier."</li>
        <li><strong>Peace of mind:</strong> "Found enough issues to renegotiate $12,000 off the price. Paid for itself 10 times over."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">How SocialProof works for home inspectors</h2>
      <ol style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
